edu.stanford.math.plex4.metric.interfaces

Interface AbstractObjectMetricSpace<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of the points in the metric space
    All Superinterfaces:
    AbstractIntMetricSpace, AbstractObjectMetric<T>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    AbstractSearchableMetricSpace<T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    EuclideanMetricSpace, ExplicitLandmarkSelector, ExplicitMetricSpace, GeometricSimplexStream, KDEuclideanMetricSpace, LandmarkSelector, MaxMinLandmarkSelector, ObjectSearchableFiniteMetricSpace, RandomLandmarkSelector, SkeletalMetric

    public interface AbstractObjectMetricSpace<T>
extends AbstractIntMetricSpace, AbstractObjectMetric<T>
    This interface defines the functionality of a finite metric space whose points are of type T. The points in the metric space are indexed by the values {0, ..., size - 1}
    Author:
    Andrew Tausz

      • getPoints

        T[] getPoints()
        This function returns the set of points in the metric space as an array. The returned array satisfies the requirement that the indices of the points in the array are equal to the indices of the points within the metric space.
        Returns:
        an array containing the points of the metric space
